as.link <-
  function(x) {
    dplyr::case_when(
      # If x is like GO:003453
      startsWith(x, "GO:") ~ paste0(
        "<a target='_blank'",
        "href='", "http://amigo.geneontology.org/amigo/term/", x, "'",
        ">", x, "</a>"
      ),
      # Otherwise try this
      TRUE ~ paste0(
        "<a target='_blank'",
        "href='", "http://www.informatics.jax.org/marker/summary?nomen=", x, "'",
        ">", x, "</a>"
      )
    )
  }
show_de_table <- function(.) {
  (.) %>%
    select(base = baseMean, l2fc = log2FoldChange, p = pvalue, padj) %>%
    ind2col("symbol") %>%
    mutate(symbol = as.link(symbol)) %>%
    DT::datatable(escape = FALSE) %>%
    DT::formatSignif(c("base", "l2fc", "p", "padj"), digits = 3)
}
show_go_table <- function(.) {
  (.) %>%
    dplyr::select("category", "overrep.p", "#DE", "#cat", "term", "GO") %>%
    DT::datatable(escape = FALSE) %>%
    DT::formatSignif("overrep.p", digits = 3)
}

make_sce <- function(counts, coldata) {
  # Check that samples in counts = genes x samples 
  # are ordered as in coldata = samples x metafields
  stopifnot(assertthat::are_equal(colnames(counts), rownames(coldata)))
  SingleCellExperiment::SingleCellExperiment(
    assays = list(counts = counts), colData = coldata
  )
}

AB – Mouse ctx & hip (10x)

About

“Mouse Whole Cortex and Hippocampus 10x” dataset from Allen Brain, 2020: [explore], [download], [protocols].

The dataset contains ~1M cells. We have selected ~31k cells of type “Astro”, “Endo” and “VLMC”.

Load

sce_abm_ch <-
  make_sce(
    counts = (
      path_to("*/AllenBrain/Mouse-WCH*/*fewer_cells/data.*.gz") %>%
        from_csv() %>%
        `[`(, sort(colnames(.)))
    ),
    coldata = (
      path_to("*/AllenBrain/Mouse-WCH*/f*cells/meta.*.gz") %>%
        from_csv() %>%
        `[`(sort(rownames(.)), )
    )

  # Only keep VLMC
  `[`(, (.)$subclass_label == "VLMC") %>%
  # Order by cell type: sometimes convenient below, esp. for plotting

Early vs late

We suppose the collection of VLMC cells is representative of a developmental trajectory. There could be a fork, but let’s partition the samples into “early” (first quarter) and “late” (last quarter) in terms of pseudotime, and find DE genes. From the PCA figure, these might correspond to two leaves of the development tree. These DE genes will narrow down the search of the “association test” below.

sce_abm_ch %<>%
  (function(sce) {
    sce$Lineage1 %>%
      list(
        is_early = ((.) < quantile((.), p = c(0.25))),
        is_late = ((.) >= quantile((.), p = c(0.75)))
      ) %>%
      with({
        sce$early <- as.factor(is_early)
        sce$late <- as.factor(is_late)

        sce
      })
  })

Overview.

sce_abm_ch$cell_type_alias_label %>%
  unique() %>%
  sort() %>%
  sapply(function(ct) {
    sce_abm_ch %>% {
      ii <- ((.)$cell_type_alias_label == ct)
      c(
        early = sum((.)$early[ii] == TRUE),
        neither = sum(((.)$early[ii] == FALSE) & ((.)$late[ii] == FALSE)),
        late = sum((.)$late[ii] == TRUE)
      )
    }
  }) %>%
  kable()

Find DE genes between “early” and “late”.

de_results.late_vs_early <-
  sce_abm_ch %>%
  # Only keep the early and the late
  `[`(, ((.)$early == TRUE) | ((.)$late == TRUE)) %>%
  {
    (.) %>%
      DESeq2::DESeqDataSet(design = ~early) %>%
      DESeq2::estimateSizeFactors() %>%
      DESeq2::DESeq(quiet = TRUE, fitType = "local") %>%
      DESeq2::results()
  } %>%
  as.data.frame() %>%
  slice_min(pvalue, n = 777)
de_results.late_vs_early %>%
  show_de_table()

GO term enrichment

Compute

# Number of early/late genes.
n <- 33
enriched_go_terms <-
  de_results.late_vs_early %>%
  {
    list(
      up_early = (.) %>% filter(log2FoldChange > 0),
      up_late = (.) %>% filter(log2FoldChange < 0)
    )
  } %>%
  lapply(function(.) {
    (.) %>%
      arrange(pvalue) %>%
      rownames()
  }) %>%
  within({
    f <- (function(x) x[1:3] %>% paste(collapse = ", "))
    print(paste("Up early:", f(up_early), "..."))
    print(paste("Up late: ", f(up_late), "..."))
    rm(f)
  }) %>%
  lapply(function(de_results) {
    de_results %>%
      data.frame(symbol = .) %>%
      slice_head(n = n) %>%
      # Get the Entrez IDs of our genes
      merge(
        org.Mm.eg.db::org.Mm.egSYMBOL2EG %>% as.data.frame(),
        by = "symbol"
      ) %>%
      pull(gene_id) %>%
      # Enrichment analysis
      limma::goana(species = "Mm") %>%
      # Limit selection
      filter(P.DE <= 0.05) %>%
      arrange(P.DE) %>%
      # Format for display
      ind2col("category") %>%
      mutate(category = as.link(category)) %>%
      rename(
        # new name = old name
        "overrep.p" = P.DE, "#DE" = DE, "#cat" = N, "GO" = Ont, "term" = Term
      )
  })

## [1] "Up late:  Itih5, Malat1, Zbtb20 ..."

Association test

From tradeSeq: associationTest is testing the null hypothesis that all smoother coefficients are equal to each other. This can be interpreted as testing whether the average gene expression is significantly changing along pseudotime.

tradeseq.assotest <-
  sce_abm_ch %>%
  # Reduce the geneset for efficiency
  `[`(rownames(de_results.late_vs_early), ) %>%
  {
    tradeSeq::fitGAM(
      (.)@assays@data$counts,
      sds = sce_abm_ch.slingshot,
      parallel = FALSE
    )
  } %>%
  tradeSeq::associationTest()

Order cells by pseudotime and genes by log-fold change (indicating early-vs-late). We normalize genewise for better visibilty.

sce_abm_ch %>%
  list(
    sce = .,
    # Order by pseudotime (drop NA's)
    pst = order((.)$Lineage1, na.last = NA),
    # Extract the lineage-associated genes
    top = tradeseq.assotest %>%
      # Some pvalue are zero => the order is not stable? => use waldStat
      slice_max(order_by = waldStat, n = 55) %>%
      rownames() %>%
      # Order by LFC (negative to positive)
      `[`(order(de_results.late_vs_early[(.), ]$log2FoldChange))
  ) %>%
  with({
    # Most-associated genes and order by pseudotime
    sce[top, pst]
  }) %>%
  {
    pheatmap::pheatmap(
      log1p((.)@assays@data$count) %>% {
        (.) / rowSums(.)
      },
      show_colnames = FALSE,
      cluster_cols = FALSE,
      cluster_rows = FALSE,
      treeheight_row = 0,
      treeheight_col = 0,
      fontsize = 6,
      color = grDevices::colorRampPalette(c("white", "black"))(10),
      annotation_col = (
        (.)@colData %>%
          as.data.frame() %>%
          select(subclass_label, cell_type_alias_label, Lineage1)
      )
    )
  }
